      "text": "You have to go, yourself, as far as you can.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "When you can't go any farther, then you're entitled to expect a miracle.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But if you stand at the edge of the water and wait until the miracle will occur, and then you will be brave enough to walk through it, then that miracle will never happen.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I have done all I could, according to my own understanding.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I ran, I didn't want to look back.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I didn't want to worry, what am I going to do in-- in Japan.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I didn't know there's going to be a committee there that will give me what to eat and a-- and a mattress to sleep on.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I ran because I knew that that is the-- it was by the singeing my-- my heels of my shoes, the war, so I ran.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I knew that you were run-- run in the direction.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "You ran away from the fire.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "You ran away from the fire.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And the rest, you are entitled to circumstances, or a miracle, whatever it called, to survive it-- no guarantees.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I could have finished up going to a prison in Shanghai, with typhoid, and not come out alive.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "There was no guarantee.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "There was no guarantees about anything.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It so happened that because I have done everything that I could-- and you know [INAUDIBLE] puts it in the mouth of Tevye in the When you're lucky, the whole thinks that you are clever.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And luck-- luck is a major component in every human life.",
      "word_count": 11
